@node RGS-Structure
struct RGS-File {
     Kennung "Poop"        (4 Bytes)
     Width=0x0000010e=270  (4 Bytes)
     Height=0x00000080=128 (4 Bytes)
     Bitplanes=0x00000040  (4 Bytes)
     ??=0x00000000         (4 Bytes)
     ??=0x00002000         (4 Bytes)
     Body                  (34560 Bytes)
     }

body : for(x=0;x<270;x++){
         for(y=0;y<128;y++){
           Colour[x,y];
           }
         }
@endnode

@node RGSRandom
RGSRandom is a program, which load a screen with a grey area, and 
the create in this area a RGS-File. The area will be saved
as a RGS-File. You have to give 2 parameter at start, the first is
the name of the RGS-File and the second is the number of the
pixels, that should be set. if a pixel will set twice, the pixel will
be the sum of both pixel.
@endnode

@node RGSSlide
RGSSlide is a program, which load a screen with a grey area, and 
the create in this area a RGS-File. The area will be saved
as a RGS-File. You have to give 2 parameter at start, the first is
the name of the RGS-File and the second is the number of the
pixels, that should be set. if a pixel will set with a random worth,
a smaller worth will be set to the right and left. It is a
special routine. It is similar to the RAMP of RGS.
@endnode
